{"id":"chai-zfb","title":"Keyed diff leaves stale DOM when switching from unkeyed to keyed children","description":"`diff_children` switches to keyed reconciliation based only on the new children list. When old children are unkeyed and new children are keyed, `diff_children_keyed` builds an empty old key map and inserts new nodes without removing old DOM nodes, leaving stale siblings in the DOM.

Repro shape: old children `[A, B]`, new children `[keyed("k", C)]` => DOM becomes `[C, A, B]`.

Fix direction: detect old keyed mode too; if mode changes across renders, either hard-fail with a clear abort or fall back to full replacement of the child list.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"gbikal@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-03-05T14:13:36Z","created_by":"Bikal Gurung","updated_at":"2026-03-05T14:13:36Z"}
